org.xchain.framework.security

Class DefaultIdentity

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.xchain.framework.security.IdentityImpl
      • org.xchain.framework.security.DefaultIdentity
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, Identity

    public final class DefaultIdentity
extends IdentityImpl
    The DefaultIdentity is an Identity with the AllPermission. It implies everything, which allows the Security API to work out of the box. Applications should either directly implement Identity or subclass IdentityImpl for more functionality.
    Author:
    Jason Rose, Christian Trimble
